1
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:23,333
I'm sure Vivian has something to
do with what your ex is doing.

2
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:26,867
Aurelia and I are just friends,
nothing more.

3
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:28,200
Are you on the same page?

4
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:29,333
What do you mean?

5
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,033
No woman will make an effort
like that

6
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,767
if she doesn't like you.

7
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,133
Aurelia?

8
00:00:34,233 --> 00:00:35,333
Hi.

9
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,900
I'll take you home.

10
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:38,300
It's Mikoy.

11
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:39,767
You're ugly here.

12
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:40,867
Look who's talking.

13
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,667
You are also not that beautiful
when you were a child.

14
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:45,067
Oh, this is the picture
of you and Mikoy

15
00:00:45,133 --> 00:00:46,567
when you were still a couple.

16
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:49,533
Why are you still keeping that,
Grandma?

17
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,900
- Give that to me.
- Why?

18
00:00:51,967 --> 00:00:53,400
I'm just showing it to her.

19
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:57,533
I know that you have forgotten
a lot about your past.

20
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:00,300
Even if you have forgotten
in your mind,

21
00:01:00,367 --> 00:01:02,100
but not in your heart.

22
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:08,633
It will take you home to
where you will be truly happy.

23
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:10,767
Did I make your life miserable?

24
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,167
I'm not just talking about
what happened here tonight.

25
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:14,667
So?

26
00:01:14,733 --> 00:01:16,833
Are you and Celeste really
getting married?

27
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:18,467
Without a doubt, yes.

28
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:19,867
Why?

29
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:22,667
Aurelia, you're creeping me out.

30
00:01:22,733 --> 00:01:24,567
Forget about my questions.

31
00:01:24,633 --> 00:01:26,367
I'm just playing...

32
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:28,133
devil's advocate.

33
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:29,833
Thanks.

34
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:35,700
No, don't meddle.

35
00:01:35,767 --> 00:01:37,300
I might get mad at you.

36
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,967
Go now.

37
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:42,167
Ms. Vangie?

38
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:43,567
Don't beg!

39
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:48,533
Sorry.

40
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,733
Thank you for saving me today.

41
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:52,367
There's a payment for that.

42
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:54,467
What's with you, Mikoy?
That's irritating.

43
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:55,500
Don't be like that.

44
00:01:55,567 --> 00:01:57,233
I'm getting married.

45
00:01:58,233 --> 00:01:59,433
So?

46
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:03,967
Okay, I'll eat this but you
should eat ten chilies.

47
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,567
Eat some more.

48
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,333
- It's ten, remember?
- Ten?

49
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:15,700
Thank you, Mikoy.

50
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:19,467
I forgot how fun it is
here in Sorsogon

51
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:23,233
and you reminded me that
in such a short amount of time.

52
00:02:25,167 --> 00:02:28,467
I left you sad in Manila
back then.

53
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:29,933
I'm just making it up to you.

54
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:34,167
Why is he doing all that?

55
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:39,033
There's only one way
to find out.

56
00:03:10,667 --> 00:03:11,767
I'll go ahead, Grandma.

57
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:13,867
You smell good.

58
00:03:15,567 --> 00:03:16,667
I always smell good.

59
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:19,200
No, sometimes you smell awful.

60
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:21,233
You...

61
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:23,533
I just put on cologne.

62
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,067
For Celeste.

63
00:03:26,967 --> 00:03:29,500
Wait, just a second.

64
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:30,533
What?

65
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:33,900
Did the old feelings resurface?

66
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:37,500
Grandma, Celeste already has
a fiancé.

67
00:03:37,567 --> 00:03:39,233
You didn't answer my question.

68
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,067
Nothing, okay?

69
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:43,300
There's no rekindling
of feelings.

70
00:03:43,367 --> 00:03:44,633
Oh my!

71
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:48,567
Grandson, why is your nose
like that?

72
00:03:48,633 --> 00:03:49,567
What?

73
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:52,267
It's growing long because you
are lying.

74
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:55,033
Ah! Gossipmonger!
Bye, Grandma.

75
00:03:55,133 --> 00:03:56,100
You have the nerve
to answer me back.

76
00:03:56,167 --> 00:03:57,533
You take care.

77
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,400
Update me.

78
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:26,067
Celeste, we will go to
a different place

79
00:04:26,133 --> 00:04:27,167
for your community service.

80
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:29,333
I'm sure you will like it.

81
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:30,667
Let's go.

82
00:04:30,733 --> 00:04:32,067
Stop it, Celeste.

83
00:04:32,133 --> 00:04:33,700
Don't push through
with your plan.

84
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,167
What's that?
Are you saying something?

85
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:39,033
Nothing.

86
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:41,867
Let's go.

87
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,267
Mikoy...

88
00:04:48,567 --> 00:04:50,467
I have to ask you something.

89
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:52,800
Sure. What is that?

90
00:04:52,867 --> 00:04:56,233
Honestly, I don't know if
I should ask you this question.

91
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,167
I will ask you.

92
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,700
Why are you doing this?

93
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:06,433
Why are you taking me to places
that are full of memories

94
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,067
of the two of us?

95
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:12,000
I know that you said it's
just work and I get that.

96
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:13,267
But...

97
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,467
I can't help but feel...

98
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:22,800
I mean, I can't help but suspect

99
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:26,633
that you're not telling me
the truth.

100
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:30,233
I don't know maybe
it's your actions...

101
00:05:31,967 --> 00:05:33,900
I don't know why are you
thinking that way?

102
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,433
Do you still love me?

103
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:40,833
Yes or no?

104
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,600
Do you still love me, Mikoy?

105
00:06:14,767 --> 00:06:18,900
I honestly hate to sound
so confrontational

106
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:21,433
and be an assuming
ex-girlfriend.

107
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:27,300
I just don't know why
you're like this to me.

108
00:06:29,467 --> 00:06:32,867
Why are you so kind to me?

109
00:06:33,633 --> 00:06:35,600
What do you think?

110
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:37,133
Why am I doing this?

111
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,833
I don't know.
I have a fiancé.

112
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:44,833
Just answer the question.

113
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:47,100
Don't make it hard for me,
Mikoy.

114
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:54,133
No.

115
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:56,067
I don't love you anymore.

116
00:06:57,467 --> 00:06:59,900
You can calm down because
there's no malice

117
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:01,633
in everything I do.

118
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,367
If there's something I want,

119
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:06,933
that is for you to bring back
the Bicolanian in you.

120
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,200
That's it.

121
00:07:12,733 --> 00:07:13,933
Good.

122
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:16,767
Okay.

123
00:07:17,967 --> 00:07:19,167
Let's go.

124
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:23,733
Why did you push through
with it?

125
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,567
You got embarrassed.

126
00:07:25,633 --> 00:07:26,900
It's humiliating.

127
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,367
Let's go.

128
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:32,500
Wait.

129
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,567
Can you manage?

130
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:21,900
Okay, we're here.

131
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,400
What are we doing here?

132
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,633
Come on, I'll help you.

133
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:33,367
I guess no need.

134
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:37,233
Welcome to Estrellado Pili Farm!

135
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:39,200
Come in.

136
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:43,100
What's the meaning of this?

137
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,667
Your next duty is here.

138
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:11,467
Have you talked with Aurelia
already?

139
00:09:12,433 --> 00:09:16,633
I believe she deserves an
apology from you

140
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,967
because of your actions
yesterday towards her.

141
00:09:20,867 --> 00:09:23,433
I already did when I helped her
yesterday

142
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,700
when her car broke down.

143
00:09:25,767 --> 00:09:27,100
That's good.

144
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:34,433
That only goes to show that
you care for her very deeply.

145
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:37,633
Which makes me think
to include her

146
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:40,133
on our next family vacation.

147
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:42,300
Sure.

148
00:09:42,367 --> 00:09:44,500
I'll bring Celeste as well.

149
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:47,833
I said, family.

150
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:50,267
Exactly, Vivian.

151
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:53,267
Celeste is also family now.

152
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:57,767
Well, not unless I accept her
as your wife...

153
00:09:57,833 --> 00:09:59,600
which will never happen.

154
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:09,467
All my life...

155
00:10:09,533 --> 00:10:12,700
I keep on seeking the approval
from others

156
00:10:12,767 --> 00:10:14,267
especially from you.

157
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:17,633
Maybe at my age,

158
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:20,867
I've already proven myself
to you, Vivian.

159
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:26,533
Maybe you won't take it badly
if I will not ask this from you.

160
00:10:27,533 --> 00:10:31,433
Because the only approval
I'm seeking right now...

161
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:33,133
is from me.

162
00:10:41,433 --> 00:10:43,433
Tonito, your chopper is here.

163
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:44,633
Thank you.

164
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,733
Now, if you'll excuse me.

165
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:04,800
Celeste, welcome again
to our farm.

166
00:11:04,867 --> 00:11:05,900
Don't worry.

167
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:07,333
I already told Mikoy

168
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:10,200
not to make your duty here
hard for you.

169
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:12,333
Why didn't you tell me
that I'll be here?

170
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,967
We're in the same house.

171
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:16,967
Celeste, you are always
in your bedroom.

172
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,533
Are you doing this on purpose?

173
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,467
Me? Why do you mean I'm doing
this on purpose?

174
00:11:26,533 --> 00:11:30,167
You know very well that my
father and I are not okay.

175
00:11:30,233 --> 00:11:32,567
And you will take me here?

176
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:33,967
I brought you here

177
00:11:34,033 --> 00:11:35,600
because Sorsogon is the
number one producer of Pili

178
00:11:35,667 --> 00:11:37,167
in the country.

179
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:38,933
And we need to promote that.

180
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,233
Really now?

181
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:42,833
Don't feel so entitled.

182
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,667
Not everything is about you.

183
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:47,267
So now, I'm the one who has
an attitude problem.

184
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:49,233
You know what, I don't want to.

185
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,633
Where are you going?

186
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,600
I quit.

187
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:57,400
I'm not going to fall victim
to your scheme.

188
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,367
Let's tell Ms. Vangie then.

189
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:05,567
That's unfair.

190
00:12:05,633 --> 00:12:08,400
No, you've reached your quota
with your attitude.

191
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:09,900
So you choose.

192
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:13,400
You will do your duty here
or I'll call Ms. Vangie

193
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:15,733
to make sure that you will
really follow.

194
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,033
You choose.

195
00:12:24,433 --> 00:12:26,633
See, you will also agree.

196
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,067
That's so soft.

197
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:09,467
Don't pound too much.

198
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:13,267
Can you stop filming, please?

199
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:25,500
I'm sorry, Celeste.

200
00:13:27,167 --> 00:13:29,767
I just want to help you
and your father.

201
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:31,267
That's why I brought you here.

202
00:13:32,467 --> 00:13:34,667
So the truth finally came out.

203
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:36,500
Thank you for your help.

204
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:37,867
But I don't need it.

205
00:13:37,933 --> 00:13:41,033
Can you give me some space?

206
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,033
More...

207
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,467
Okay.

208
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,267
- Oh no!
- Why?

209
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:18,967
Cynthia and Brooke got
ahead of us

210
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:21,533
with the locations and products
that we researched.

211
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,167
Tiff?

212
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,000
Can I see?

213
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,100
I'll take care of it,
don't worry.

214
00:14:44,167 --> 00:14:45,567
What's that?

215
00:14:45,633 --> 00:14:47,333
My peace offering.

216
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,833
I'm sorry about what happened
the other day.

217
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:52,333
I know I went out of hand.

218
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:55,133
I don't know what to say.

219
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:58,467
You're always like that.

220
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:05,633
Tiff, I swear, that's the last.

221
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:07,433
We won't fight again.

222
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:16,333
Can you forgive me?

223
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:29,767
You can have this.

224
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,167
Thank you.

225
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,467
Wow!

226
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:36,933
Hey, I like that.

227
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:40,600
So you accepted my gift...

228
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:43,833
but not me.

229
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,767
He has a point, Tiff.

230
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:51,633
Fine.

231
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:03,100
Can I have?

232
00:16:07,033 --> 00:16:08,367
Thank you.

233
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:18,833
Sebastian, you should help
Celeste.

234
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:22,967
Don't worry,
Celeste is a fighter.

235
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:26,367
And besides, she always fights
with us.

236
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:28,633
You're full of nonsense.

237
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:30,767
I'll be the one to approach her.

238
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:31,900
You?

239
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,167
Mother?

240
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,167
Hey, Love.

241
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:36,633
- I'm okay.
- What's with you?

242
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:38,200
Are you dizzy?

243
00:16:38,267 --> 00:16:41,667
When you get older,
you become dizzy.

244
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:44,033
- I'll go to Celeste.
- Are you alright?

245
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,067
Yes.

246
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,767
Celeste, I'll help you.

247
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,567
Do you know how to break open
a Pili nut?

248
00:17:00,633 --> 00:17:05,167
My mother taught me
when I was young so I know.

249
00:17:05,233 --> 00:17:06,900
I can do it on my own.

250
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,133
Thank you.

251
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:37,167
I can't contact Tiffany.

252
00:17:38,567 --> 00:17:40,567
Give her space.

253
00:17:40,633 --> 00:17:42,467
She still feels bad about you.

254
00:17:43,867 --> 00:17:45,033
I know.

255
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:47,467
It's just frustrating sometimes.

256
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:49,467
That's how it really is.

257
00:17:49,567 --> 00:17:54,067
They say no matter how good
you are as a businessman...

258
00:17:54,133 --> 00:17:55,233
nothing will prepare you

259
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:58,267
for the most difficult
business deal in your life,

260
00:17:58,333 --> 00:17:59,800
your daughter.

261
00:18:02,067 --> 00:18:03,633
Yeah, I know.

262
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:06,600
I hope she can accept
my decision and Celeste's.

263
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:09,867
A little more patience.

264
00:18:09,933 --> 00:18:14,233
I tell you, like any other
business deals...

265
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:16,633
that one is going to be
worth it.

266
00:18:32,767 --> 00:18:35,200
Did you drive away Ms. Adora?

267
00:18:35,267 --> 00:18:36,600
Of course not.

268
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:37,800
Don't assume.

269
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,667
I will not die.

270
00:18:56,733 --> 00:18:59,100
See, I can still do this.

271
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:15,133
Lucinda, my Love.

272
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:18,833
Not long ago, we only go
to this place to stroll.

273
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:21,800
Now we own this.

274
00:19:21,867 --> 00:19:24,867
I hope we can make this place
flourish.

275
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:27,200
Yes of course,
you of all people, Love.

276
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:29,000
We will help each other.

277
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:33,167
We will make this flourish
like our love.

278
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:35,100
Of course, Love.

279
00:19:35,167 --> 00:19:38,633
And you know, once this place
becomes successful,

280
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:40,400
I'll build a hut.

281
00:19:40,467 --> 00:19:43,067
So when Celeste is on vacation,

282
00:19:43,133 --> 00:19:46,767
the three of us will be together
in that hut, right?

283
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:48,100
Yes.

284
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:53,433
But Love, can we build a small
store for my sewn clothes?

285
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,000
Yes Love, of course.

286
00:19:55,067 --> 00:19:58,067
Anything is possible.

287
00:19:58,133 --> 00:19:59,200
How about you, Celeste?

288
00:19:59,267 --> 00:20:00,300
What do you want?

289
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:02,467
I want a swimming pool

290
00:20:02,567 --> 00:20:07,133
and a big coliseum
for my fashion shows.

291
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,433
Is that really what you want?

292
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:09,467
Yes.

293
00:20:09,533 --> 00:20:13,733
Okay, we'll build a lot
of coliseums.

294
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:20,433
We'll name it Celeste Diazta
Estrellado Coliseum.

295
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:22,800
Thank you, Father.

296
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,067
It's you, not me.

297
00:20:44,567 --> 00:20:48,633
I'm sorry, Grandma Ikay, Mikoy.

298
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:54,700
I don't know where to go
anymore.

299
00:20:54,767 --> 00:20:57,167
Sorry if I always eat here.

300
00:20:58,767 --> 00:21:04,300
Celeste, did you ask permission
from Patricio and Adora

301
00:21:04,367 --> 00:21:06,667
that you will come here?

302
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:10,433
Is it your brother's first
birthday today?

303
00:21:10,533 --> 00:21:11,900
Sebastian?

304
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:15,333
Yes...

305
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,200
that's why I left the house.

306
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:27,067
I don't want to see them happy.

307
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:32,767
The more I get hurt.

308
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:37,667
I feel that I'm not a part
of their family.

309
00:21:38,267 --> 00:21:42,900
Celeste, they are still
your family.

310
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,333
Why can't I feel it?

311
00:21:47,533 --> 00:21:50,367
I feel that I'm not part
of the family.

312
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:55,467
Ever since my mother died,
my life is a mess.

313
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:57,900
I understand.

314
00:21:57,967 --> 00:22:00,600
I know that what happened hurts.

315
00:22:01,467 --> 00:22:04,233
But maybe they are already
worried about you.

316
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:07,600
I'm sure your father,
Patricio,

317
00:22:07,667 --> 00:22:08,900
and your mother, Adora,
are looking for you.

318
00:22:08,967 --> 00:22:11,500
She is not my mother,
Grandma Ikay.

319
00:22:13,633 --> 00:22:18,300
I only have one mother and
no one can replace her.

320
00:22:19,733 --> 00:22:24,400
Grandma Ikay, my mother died
because of them.

321
00:22:29,267 --> 00:22:33,400
I only have one mother,
just one.

322
00:23:10,467 --> 00:23:12,867
It's you, not me.

323
00:23:19,367 --> 00:23:21,167
Can we go home?

324
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,567
What do you mean go home?
We just arrived.

325
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:30,333
Celeste, look, I'm sorry.

326
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:33,667
I didn't know you're that angry
with your father.

327
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:38,600
Well, I appreciate your concern.

328
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:41,933
Please, next time don't meddle.

329
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,733
You're just messing things up.

330
00:23:45,767 --> 00:23:46,933
Celeste?

331
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:27,367
If I were Celeste,
I'll be scared.

332
00:24:27,433 --> 00:24:29,300
Aurelia is just not in love,
she's obsessed.

333
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,400
Where is father?

334
00:24:30,467 --> 00:24:31,900
He left early.

335
00:24:31,967 --> 00:24:33,500
He said he has an important
matter to attend to.

336
00:24:33,567 --> 00:24:34,733
An important matter
to attend to?

337
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,900
This beach is the next
biggest tourist destination

338
00:24:36,967 --> 00:24:38,433
in this place.

339
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,800
You can choose a location here.

340
00:24:40,867 --> 00:24:42,267
Father is still not here.

341
00:24:42,333 --> 00:24:43,667
Don't worry, he's coming.

342
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:46,167
Celeste still see me
as your mistress,

343
00:24:46,233 --> 00:24:47,200
even if we got married,

344
00:24:47,267 --> 00:24:49,700
even if we're now husband
and wife.

345
00:24:49,767 --> 00:24:52,800
Yes, we were completely wrong
when we hurt Lucinda.

346
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:54,000
But when I loved you,

347
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:56,000
I didn't know that you already
have a family.

348
00:24:56,067 --> 00:24:57,500
I have a bad feeling.

349
00:24:57,567 --> 00:24:58,600
Maybe she will not come home.

350
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:00,000
Celeste is old enough.

351
00:25:00,067 --> 00:25:01,600
She already knows
what she's doing.

352
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:04,733
I will not go home until I find
your Manay .

353
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:07,700
What's with that Basti and you
agreed with his suggestions?

354
00:25:07,767 --> 00:25:09,200
Are you jealous, Babe?

355
00:25:09,267 --> 00:25:10,933
I know his intention is bad.

356
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,100
You choose.

357
00:25:12,167 --> 00:25:14,833
You continue with your jealousy
or we fail?

358
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:17,700
Is there any way to speed up
her community service?

359
00:25:17,767 --> 00:25:19,900
I already talked to the Mayor.

360
00:25:19,967 --> 00:25:21,233
He didn't agree.

361
00:25:21,300 --> 00:25:22,600
Did you negotiate with them?

362
00:25:22,667 --> 00:25:24,333
Maybe we can just give
a donation.

363
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:26,833
I don't want to ruin our
wedding preparations

364
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,633
just because of her community
service.

365
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:30,000
I thought you knew me.

366
00:25:30,067 --> 00:25:31,333
Why does it seem like
you don't know me?

367
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:33,667
You've changed a lot, Celeste.

368
00:25:33,733 --> 00:25:35,600
I've been trying to reach
her earlier

369
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,333
and I can't seem to get through.

370
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,067
She's been out of range.

371
00:25:39,133 --> 00:25:40,867
Maybe her phone is off.

372
00:25:40,933 --> 00:25:42,600
Why would she do that?

373
00:25:42,667 --> 00:25:45,767
She knows that we call
each other every now and then.

374
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:48,100
I don't think she will
turn off her phone.
